[Both human and monkey yellow fever cases have been occurring in Santa Clara this year (2021). The number of human cases has increased from 2 reported on 11 Mar 2021 (see Yellow fever - Americas (05): Brazil (SC) human, monkey 20210315.8247346) to 3, and now to 7 reported above. These human cases represent spillover from the sylvan (forest) transmission cycle. Fortunately, there has been no urban yellow fever transmission in Brazil since 1942. Increased surveillance is important to know where yellow fever virus transmission is taking place. People living in or visiting these localities should be vaccinated to avoid more human cases. - Mod.TY

